[{"Name":"Cal Cohen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIYyjzI0behNDtmO7PzpUsM-zMvPOQLH6JBZhMTAU_xWnDexg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best brunch in all of Israel! Went for breakfast and got the Pancakes, the egg and cheese, and the lavender latte. They do an amazing job at making the latte so flavorful without making it too sweet. The pancakes were amazing and had a very good berry topping. The egg and cheese was also so flavorful and had these sweet caramelized onions on top that was the perfect addition. Amazing music and very friendly waiters/waitresses. Perfect atmosphere! 11/10 experience highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shira Salton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKra5Gk0SJjsuJbGNKZXE9tWUNarQnwfQjrWZDa7dGADIx29A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourite places in Tel Aviv(but only on weekdays!!). The food and coffee are excellent, and everything is of the highest quality. However, the prices are quite high ,especially those of the drinks(27 shekels for matcha!!). Great vegan options, sweet and savoury. On weekends it tends to be very crowded and the wait might last a long time, which isn't so fun on sunny or rainy days. So I recommend visiting on weekdays when the traffic is much lighter.  The service varies between excellent and poor, depends on the waiter. Recommended!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAIYfm-NWNZu5uDB2CbqfSdUL5brNlMEEf6mBl&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"Olga Kostur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzkWunUFnZuZCe6KJr-bugW8_58qizbx2Q_eiv4obn3CIuUB80Fw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing breakfast place! Vibrant, lots of people, and music is playing! The staff is attentive â¤ï¸

Food was great as well, fantastic design of the menu  - healthy and classical options with an original take on them. Pancakes, granola, bagels!

Oat and almond-rice milk available, which is fantastic for us :))","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGNfVCk7MfCgTksCU0tJJxFUkZ2P2T6L3elPML&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2022-10-21"},{"Name":"jacob goldshtein","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXo72d68fWM6K2GxspfvmUh2C6GW9u0MathakLJYn4klK3TGrhnxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely amazing brunch experience in Tel Aviv. Food was amazing, drinks were delicious, staff was super friendly and place was beautiful. Canâ€™t recommend this place enough especially if your a bagel lover. Would definitely return again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPw72mMhlaXs7roDU8GC2Ni8QID3PXhPwSnjkvk&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2023-5-7"},{"Name":"×œ×™×œ×š-×’×•×œ×“×™ ××¨×’×•×œ×™×Ÿ","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOXObyZLDhmvq9pA4EFHgX0Jg5KH3LCHheMfILYY-AT6J1bJk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We waited for more than 30 minutes just for 2 bagels. The â€œEggs Nâ€™ Cheese Bagelâ€ was supposed to include a fried runny egg, and the egg was fully cooked.
We asked all 5 waiters for water and, at last, one of them brought it.
In addition for service not being amazing, we were emotionally pressured to add a service fee (tip, which is not included) and also the minimum fee is at 10%. The waitress literally said â€œour salary is only tipsâ€..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMdFNCvk2lodOzU6GA2-OKz-HzEulUSwqwUVChC&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"Franco Ruben Vargas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYrVmui_HIvy7EN7K2x-zOiGfZKqTrPNFh5nDhxBq7OmJxcUI3aA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious place for a gluten free, vegetarian or dairy free options. The place is quiet and nice with a self service concept. You order in the front counter and you pick up in the bar. All of their options are delicious and healthy from main courses to beverages. Pick from different milk alternatives and be clear if you want the GF or totally vegan options. Recommended for breakfast at anytime. I had pancakes and bagels at 3 pm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORrvXpbFMAqnPLD9hpajQ3o454gnB_STCC6dZH&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2022-3-23"},{"Name":"Epolina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKij04P_BqvHAkkyfVJqz8x79730MHkBNjo7E4iggbvBo8xLgCDA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I went twice in the past week. First time I ordered pancakes that were delicious.
Second time I ordered the famous beer bread breakfast dish. Unfortunately, it was not good. Toasted bread with sauce and fried egg was nice, but nectarine was absolutely unripened, sour, very thick and hot from the egg. I barely could eat it. Now looking back, I should've returned it.
I thought to take over star out because of it. But the place is so nice and cozy, friendly staff, quick service and superb coffee.
My advice: please use ripe fruits and thinner cuts.
Upd. I went today again, ordered pink granola, it was very pretty, but for my taste the dish was very unbalanced, a little bit chia pudding, that is tasteless and a lot of granola, couldn't finish half of it, fruits also were not sweet.
Sorry that I didn't order a bagel, looked much more promising. Taking one star off.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR-NrvGXHZq5oTPAao2uM5CTyyKBIillx5sMx6&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2020-7-21"},{"Name":"Daniel Bar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_LVV_ck0ipJg_C1WVU9PBNAWTKEtaYEDYpGbSP6Ghhh_4Yg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fresh, young, positive, atmospheric, busy, hyper Tel-Avivian coffee shop. Both coffee and food are top notch, made with love and attention to detail.
Note that you should stand in line to order, then you sit and wait for the counter to call your name. Great place for soaking some local atmosphere and people watching. If you see a long line (sometimes reaching the street), donâ€™t get discouraged, as service is pretty fast.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYXjL-nJ6CIVSNrNPyV6TGqUOSZcGtZvKI5A6M&fid=0x0:0x5042104dca7eae73"],"When":"2022-6-12"}]

[{"Name":"Rupert A.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLc1z9bLynhgKGkihxX-cpS9pSPodymkNd2IFPssLXm5QGQeA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What stood out most to me was the friendly and attentive service by the host.  He was genuinely friendly and caring.
Please note that they have a "happy hour" on alcoholic beverages as well as a special lunch menu from noon till 4pm.
We arrived at 3:45 pm but missed it since it took them till after 4pm to take our order.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOzFBJk0J-gYyvcQiA_Idt5ej6TP7w1VT-1OYL-&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2022-3-24"},{"Name":"Caitlin Treloar-Ward","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVz0pnrLHBCbxLUIdjyGRBdtKcUCRz_Y6K8G3IQGyP3qI7lQqQhbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Beautiful little spot, expansive menu for small and large dishes.
Calabrese toasted sandwich and the shakshuka were ordered.
When we went to pay, we werenâ€™t asked to leave a tip or had the option, our card was swiped and we were off. Sorry about that, we would have liked to have done the right thing ğŸŒˆ","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNCqX54uCPAHyrxEwU6DzlLG7ZQ_4YE-bC4EpHE&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2022-7-30"},{"Name":"Alex Frazier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUB5LMa-E6QAUeiAzedbdJCbkyB008tb5iNbqOOcbmrM8yjBVPz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dizengoff Cafe is a great place to stop in for a quick coffee, or to stay for breakfast or lunch. The inside is very cute and the patio is the perfect place to sit and people watch. I highly recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxhZMHzWqavWzwOZP2mJPwiC4uLuYLcz9m4Wct&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2023-9-26"},{"Name":"Niv Shimoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKC_NTN_3jBQaO39EWMTRMDNxltkCNxFPlx77COe2wTH3h1sHifA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A great coffee shop in the middle of Dizengoff St. The decoration of the place is very delicate and beautiful. I really like the atmosphere, this is one of the best things in this city. food was excellent, I ate the Roasted Salad and it was very special. the flavors are very surprising, fresh and refreshing. what I like the most is the taste of the ginger in the salad dressing.
The bruschetta was tasty but overpriced. staff is friendly and polite.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOlNK8wu1BE2UYmpoB9ch_grfgdSJPe86D54Tcf&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2018-2-27"},{"Name":"Mindaugas Vaiskunas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXV1XstWgpKxn2Yaz_x7eoE23j4XXMZpfRRBVyEm84evAqdXK9sVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of visiting Cafe Dizengoff, and I must say, it was an excellent experience. The cafe has a cozy atmosphere that immediately made me feel comfortable and welcome. The food was absolutely delicious, and I was particularly impressed with the shakshuka with feta and the toast with gouda and buche cheese. It's not surprising that Cafe Dizengoff is a popular destination, as the food and atmosphere are both great. I highly recommend this cafe to anyone looking for a delicious meal in a warm and inviting setting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAFrAR_dahjRB56SrLPoZ6S5svV_Z9iGGz31P9&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2023-3-20"},{"Name":"Mary Grant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXG4TwuDMP1JtCNcJ2Mj_TGPANaoLorac7uFTUhqD5rD-iZNg4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A big choice of breakfast dishes as well as regular menu. We tried crispy chicken sandwich and Mesahan (chicken on the bread with tahini and species). Both dishes were huge, we didnâ€™t manage to finish it. The sandwich was nothing special, came with a spicy sauce - I would not recommend to take it. Mesahan was very unique mix of tastes and spices, weâ€™ve never tried anything like this. It was also very filling and good for sharing.

The place was full on Friday afternoon, all tables outside were taken. Amazing vibes and a lovely view on a busy Dizengoff street.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQ1XsLnPlOUkBXO2cTBN37DFbfvGu-p6YtMZZY&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2023-3-31"},{"Name":"Lihi Bavli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDrsJ54hPaascFr9Yiu7t0PP56Szf5z_v0BUYErt3agnvaX5DeMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Iâ€™ve been here multiple times for breakfast afternoon coffee or dinner. I love the variety of the menu and all dishes or very good, fresh and tasteful. The service is always great and I really love the music.
It does get a little bit busy sometimes you have to wait in line for a table.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOLx4uDms2n4wAb0R8ufDwQgEoytJtmyf1vVHh-&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2021-8-17"},{"Name":"michelle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU28g7bMDgS8xYgyafala8XDJKUjNo4MDVxjdxqxwuCwiyleCuSTQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"food was great and the portions were even better- the single breakfast was huge! a nice inexpensive stop for breakfast with an authentic tel avivian atmosphere. The service was amazing and they even handed us free ice cream since it was so hot outside! Only thing is the place is usually really crowded and in our case the people that sat beside us really didnâ€™t respect personal space so it wasnâ€™t the greatest experience in that aspect- unfortunately we couldnâ€™t really converse or eat properly because they were constantly smoking right on us and talking loudly. Itâ€™s not the cafeâ€™s fault but do keep in mind that the place could get crowded especially on Fridays.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmuXj0vWB2tNgQZTf9W2oW5UfESZ95kr1jgPIQ&fid=0x0:0x7e4bed0868c78530"],"When":"2021-6-4"}]

The vibe is nice. Very kind staff. Prices are ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOMM6uX2l0EwzRVvdZU0fcWXh6kD-6wyO2q2ynV&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2022-3-12"},{"Name":"sharif sweilem","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWGdrejLm6Ql5YW4QX3BvDOnOBGGUjrZy-akNo1y3B2Jmizl5f2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's very delicious, the atmoshper is  traditional with songs of fairouz, we ordered zaatar, labnah, hummus, green zaatar with cheese and two lemonades it costs us 205 NIS","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOovmd4OyPWOvFz5LiBsIY16-a7K4K0tyRBO-Ia&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2023-7-25"},{"Name":"Yelle G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1FMysoxRDm9sVp7F5Q9GCQWIkqYq1-gCz7GP1dW8xEGxikTeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee and Knafa are the most delicious â¤ï¸ just for them you can come ğŸ˜â˜€ï¸

Arabic coffee here is not just coffee. It is a deep and intense symphony of flavors, rich in spice notes, with bitterness and a slightly sweet aftertaste. It is served in traditional small cups, and each sip is imbued with oriental magic, leading to a world of soft pillows, incense and warm hospitality.

And now about Knaf. This is a sweet that can easily become the queen of any dessert table. Made with carefully selected ingredients, it is soft and tender, with a crispy golden crust and delicate sweet cheese inside. It is served warm, soaked in fragrant syrup, with the addition of fresh nuts. Now this is one of my favorite places, I recommend it to everyone â¤ï¸","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQH_N7xePYi2TwQvpl7s45oMv1YmVq5amTuQkY&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2023-2-6"},{"Name":"Niv Shimoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKC_NTN_3jBQaO39EWMTRMDNxltkCNxFPlx77COe2wTH3h1sHifA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Authentic Arab cafe, you can feel here the warm hospitality. they are welcome and very nice. the food is ok there hummus, salads and knaffe and more from the Arab kitchen. the place located in beautiful area, the heart of old Jaffa. very special atmosphere all over the neighborhood. the sea is just 3 min walk away. they have so many Hookah taste here and almost everyone smoke.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPftf8DKExaLBXCTSdp4YLM3KBKAyJd03lV54_N&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2018-5-9"},{"Name":"Elena Serena Piccardi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKfchDorSxNYCgZhioGbYJjDrJJjUKR8CSxSbtE0PZRiaH2CVL5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We bumped into this little gem while strolling around Jaffa and had an amazing lunch! Great vegetarian options and huge portions! Smoothies also recommended! Definitely a perfect spot for a quick, recharging lunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlKtLHI8f0OZEqHw88I5cqQ0LINwQe7sycfimc&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2019-2-9"},{"Name":"joseph saadeh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9Hk7kNLq6-ySBhZYcoLt9vOjLsWOFWTQfS1dG8QBATcp6tpGohg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"OMG... food is really good.. good shisha.. prices are affordable.. the location is very close to the old city (two minutes on foot) and the old sea port of jaffa.. looks more local and reflects more the traditional jaffa unlike other restaurant that are made for tourists.. historically this cafe is the very same cafe that the fishing men use to sit in the thirty's of the last century when they come back from the sea in the morning..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP11dpf-UzKNG2l90xn-30lMeP07dCQnZk1ql6_&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2020-2-28"},{"Name":"Ema BUDAEVA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUFUSCm5f-asXVAcW3k0MvSCR3cwQ1qJHwMaSvAB4mjEREGZHEE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Open on Saturday.
We ordered kebab. It was so hard, like stone. But the staff is nice and they agree to change plate .
So, the price is quite high for kebab - 55","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPP451jIOh3bGpNS-8j-VVD9ZuwI14ytE9YPvCn&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2022-4-2"},{"Name":"YoÃ«l Knopf","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKYq7LPaFpWBqjJvW1ztipsHcxn022myz4dUZoZ48ohecbX9my=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A nice little place with a decent selection of tasty local, and some continental, dishes.  A good place to stop and relax during your day of walking/site-seeing, maybe even with a hooka/shisha/nargila.  Service can be slow at times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzL2FjFopelLtHXwU0vPk-Em2l6mgHpMRGyuoC&fid=0x0:0x8e86b48d06a7112f"],"When":"2019-11-21"}]

It's the place you feel welcomed and you know nobody will rush you to leave. The only sad thing was that the cinnamon babka was lacking cinnamon, but it was delicious nonetheless!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marco Tullio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX61tPZxnJLUG9b6kaeht8E4Rpkvo7bJ0VV4wBCQBvP1bcxD_De1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Let me tell you about this amazing cafe in the Florentin neighborhood of Tel Aviv. Not only does it serve delicious tuna sandwiches and cappuccinos, but it also boasts a lush and green ambiance with plenty of plants. It's the perfect place to relax and enjoy your favorite book under the shade of beautiful trees.

This cafe has created a tranquil oasis amidst the bustling streets of Florentin. The abundance of plants creates a refreshing and calming atmosphere that invites you to unwind and escape into your own little world. With cozy seating areas nestled under the trees, you can find the perfect spot to settle in with your book and enjoy some quiet time.

When it comes to the food and drinks, this cafe doesn't disappoint. Their tuna sandwiches are packed with flavor and made with fresh ingredients. Whether you prefer a classic recipe or a unique twist, each bite will leave you satisfied. And of course, don't forget to pair your sandwich with a delicious cappuccino for the ultimate treat.

Not only is this cafe a haven for bookworms and plant lovers, but it also captures the essence of the Florentin neighborhood. Its laid-back and friendly atmosphere reflects the artistic and bohemian vibe of the area, making it a favorite spot among locals and visitors alike.

So, if you're looking for a unique and enchanting cafe in Florentin, Tel Aviv, where you can enjoy mouthwatering tuna sandwiches and cappuccinos amidst a green oasis, this is the place for you. Grab your favorite book, find a cozy spot under the trees, and immerse yourself in the serene ambiance of this delightful cafe.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdYom6ZJA1_nFdSdO54r8QIUWwLiVrlTNCpocu&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2023-6-11"},{"Name":"Niv Shimoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKC_NTN_3jBQaO39EWMTRMDNxltkCNxFPlx77COe2wTH3h1sHifA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Florentin neighborhood well know as a hipster and cool place. beautiful coffee with fantastic seating area in and out side. the inside is old style decoration very gentle and clean. the service is good and itâ€™s open from early morning.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVFDSu-oiW05t_ptysN7ueHtcO3EbuEWrdW-BV&fid=0x0:0xbb3f8fd4b85ecc87"],"When":"2021-6-10"},{"Name":"Ermis Makis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPJYBFuTNy9p6e73zqGQhvA6fb6h_kDbsWCQ5Y8g32hSAfDgY8sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A lively, hipstery, corner cafÃ© that serves great pastries and coffee. [{"Name":"Shira Salton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKra5Gk0SJjsuJbGNKZXE9tWUNarQnwfQjrWZDa7dGADIx29A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The coffee is very good, and the place is really nice. However, the chocolate chip cookie I tried was quite dry and not so tasty. The price is average to a specialty coffee in Tel Aviv. I had bought some beans which were great, but when I had asked whether it's fare trade the cashier had no idea what I was talking about. So I'm pretty sure it's not fare trade;) Nice place","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUKkQqliGvK7iVYlVucLBe5sX5F9YHCyhQa44I&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2023-9-26"},{"Name":"RAVE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZkEtNCn047-jM4dPo37rcR69TYzKQQ9RPQ0ETwVOXUhBSVz89Sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Updating ğŸ˜ itâ€™s been a while, I hope that now everybody is welcome as I do like this place.

Unfortunately I had to change my review, iâ€™ve been thrown away after sitting in this coffee shop many times saying that â€œ you canâ€™t get in if you eating non-kosher foodâ€ ğŸ˜±
I find it very disturbing when people allow themselves to be racist or homophobic or whatever extreme idea it was.
The same way that I would never tell somebody that he cannot get into the place because he only eats kosher food it is not OK to say the opposite if my views are different.
I decided to put three stars instead of one to allow them to apologize and civilized.

One of my favorite coffee shops in Tel Aviv, iâ€™d like it because itâ€™s both casual and very chic.
I love spending time there at my morning and have my luxury coffee :) itâ€™s super tasty and super high-quality.
The coffee is deep in flavor and made to perfection.
They should definitely upgrade their sandwiches but nothing will stop me from grabbing another cup of coffee at this place.
I just love it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNlHhFwTYSr_NPDZHhvfj-n2G8wl6YL3RHBNmX4&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2018-7-1"},{"Name":"Ido Simyoni","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzkOoy_rh-Crbnc6Ql2Y0qqZ1-C34qzmepjSCd8YvsG7BJRyG8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stunning professional with  hipster vibe coffeeshop. Loved my oat milk latte . Bought even coffee to take home to nyc with me. I like that they asked me if I wanted it in a mug or glass (glass rules). Service was beyond friendly","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_lI9Ae4olBolAEi9vDbqkhOwCY2JM43DenhLg&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2022-5-6"},{"Name":"Michael Olshansky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXX61wd2boH8NVva-SQMZH9kDolVUM2Mh4GZQmKDkjjh_pkPgNVew=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Seriously the best coffee in the area. Not your typical Aroma experience (bo-oring). Hi tech kids and hip Tel Avivians surround you. I definitely recommend for a refreshing break or just an informal meeting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYnAt1246ERntTia064Se4yZ2BaSfKr_AgY4M8&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2019-1-26"},{"Name":"Bene Garcia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIY9M6ia4pGO8GpCGP2uE1q8bmJg6Ksba8vXYh1YeVGKIHUcbg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best damn coffee in Israel, in days! Definitly up there with any hipster shop anywhere in the world. Got the grey blend, supposed to be tilting bitter. But it's awesome- crema is good, oil is good, temp is good, atmosphere is good. I'd give it 7-stars if i can. Worth a visit, worth a repeat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuU02vG6fhEeI8i-9o_NIbdfNG8DhC5ZxVGGVN&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2022-11-22"},{"Name":"Adam Shoshani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHVDy4icfezelaHD7P9ssa0n8bEG3hlx5dNkFj4enZVXsClatlRg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"WayCup Mikveh is probably my favorite coffee shop in Tel-Aviv. Where do I start?

The coffee is roasted locally and is simply delicious. WayCup offers a range of changing single-origin coffee beans from around the world prepared in a range of brewing methods.

The owners and the baristas are some of the nicest and most friendly people around, in short, people who love what they do (coffee) and about their customers.

Whether you are just stopping by for a quick coffee (it's literally 3 min walk from Rothschild Blvd.) or if you want to open a laptop and work there for the day, highly recommend this place. Enjoy!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOA11ReK7nOJTns2rkMkCEIXiZnfSjaXQWQ_siD&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2018-11-6"},{"Name":"Roy Paz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJXf90d-wMIdjDpYOFXlZvkuY2O5UIv4YLe9fmaFpCOwemroeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally got around to giving WayCup Coffee a shot after hearing great things about it for over a year now.....
And I'm happy to report that they definitely live up to the hype! ğŸ™ƒ

I came here this morning to get one iced coffee and a small pastry. The plan was to order, pay, & enjoy the coffee and cigarettes while sitting at the tables outside, & then heading off to begin the rest of my day...

I ended up staying here for about 3 1/2 hours without even fully noticing (or caring)ğŸ˜‹.
The coffee here is absolutely perfect & the prices are standard /average for a Tel Avivian coffee shop. But the thing that makes WayCup unique in my opinion is; a) the people here - (the workers as well as the customers), & b) how friendly they are...

The other customers I met while sitting at the table outside were so friendly and laid back, that my introverted, shy, & quiet self, ended up speaking to 3 different, random people who I've never met before & it felt completely natural.

Each of the 3 people chose to sit right next to me - at the table directly next to mine. - these 3 people came separately & at different times obviously) and there was such a friendly vibe + straight up good conversations with random strangers.

One was an amazing artist who was drawing while drinking his coffee, the 2nd person is an employee at Facebook who was really interesting and cool to speak with, & the 3rd person was just a cool woman (I didn't ask what she does haha).

Anyways I ended up ordering two more coffees because they were so delicious and I was thoroughly enjoying myself....

So from my original plan of a quick iced coffee + one little pastry before heading off, I had 3 coffees with the pastry and stayed for 3+hrs.

*THE MAIN REASON I VISITED WAYCUP COFFEE IN THE FIRST PLACE*:

They're one of the VERY few places in Israel that sell Flat Whites (...if not the only one? - I honestly can't say for sure because l really haven't looked into it; but it's definitely the only coffee shop I've ever seen in Israel with Flat White on the menu).

The coffee is strong, fresh, & extremely tasty.
It's honestly addicting in a way that other coffees aren't.

All in all:
A) Great service
B) Great pastries
C) Great atmosphere
D) What else could you ask for?

By far one of the best Coffee Shops in this city. I already can't wait to return ğŸ˜‹","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMiTHQiXXVuCOkTWXdRHqA5E7AA9HwSOCbwWv_Z&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2020-9-9"},{"Name":"TamÃ¡s Olasz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLufk7RJ2KVpNo_UoU2BIDITyx-L8efn-C2JeYj7XhxoQyecVdN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great coffee, nice service, pleasant atmosphere. One of the best places to get specialty coffee in Tel Aviv.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbGfpZ6PYhurbtGBDRnADPPV7mLAq8MsnANd2Z&fid=0x0:0xbf7b786183e34391"],"When":"2023-8-11"}]

Cortado was more like espresso macchiato,  but pistachio- raspberry muffin was perfect!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lory CM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVeUph9xhJBBu-swNP4HuB14kcNRQ2REPG7M9rRQDkGL4QPgaTndA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's one of my best cafe list to sip matcha. Well I'm kinda upset with their sandwich buns this time it was hard for me to chew, I really couldn't munch all because of its hardness.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thomas Dafinger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVgRxfBp6VMIHfTWsantiboN_3wV3cKgrdCUr_knYj_-dXSrU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"When you enter this restaurant you have to place and pay your order at the register. They provide a beeper when the food items are ready to pick up. I had a shakshouka and a gouda sandwich. The shakshouka came with a bread and a side salad on a tray and this tray was not cleaned properly. I donâ€™t understand in no case, why they donâ€™t use a tiny plate or bowl for this salad as this is absolutely unhygienic when lying on the tray separated by a thin and sodden baking paper only! But the shakshouka itself was good. The gouda sandwich was ok in taste, but I personally donâ€™t need the green pesto sauce on it, as the cheese taste is almost fully lost.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORcYY-5vXxBeanD3NlZ07hSbJxWcm6cPnR93k&fid=0x0:0x9e6eb164f0846581"],"When":"2023-7-3"},{"Name":"Doron Magen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUs9fJWbQDVLLhw5isyintxyPU8Y8dYDMG4WMa6AmNeraocVqA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"So I only tried their â€œBarzilay Breakfastâ€ which by the name I assume is their flagship Israeli breakfast, and itâ€™s just so weird and non Israeli which just made me disappointed. user_reviews: [{"Name":"arielaw4","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsuj2Hj3lxa_fnNvw9aMNUOst4RbgtS28KLhG8G5ut10VbSA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don't often give 5 stars. Came here because people keep mentioning it as their favourite cafe and now I know why. My wife got the pesto mushroom bruschetta and I got the eggs breakfast that came with a coffee and juice, and incredible dips. Each dip was the best made dip of its kind I have ever had. And they offered us more bread which was a very nice touch. They were super busy and yet attentive to us. Everything about this place was superb. All you need to have a great start for your day","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNEHYm33y5MxsipVhpCv5eh_-MveTfrMwjXUZia&fid=0x0:0x8b0db5dcd7f73a74"],"When":"2022-12-22"},{"Name":"Meir Pechthalt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqxLDzuxMZjg5-aTa8T34nzlDU-n_xjzH4etTpmQFpIyeLSmx9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A healing place for mind and body!

In addition, there is also a fruit and vegetable stand that adds to the relaxed atmosphere of the place.
warmly recommended!!","Images":null,"When":""}]
